The paper deals with image processing techniques, specifically super-resolution, using deep neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of adversarial training and cycle consistency also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The application of the proposed framework to endomicroscopy images suggests a potential fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of physically-inspired constraints also suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep neural networks for image processing suggests a potential fit for the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
